1%2C%20there%20are%20more%20people%20in%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-unemployment-claims-rising-most-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elooking%20for%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20there%20are%20open%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lackluster%20job%20market%20is%20yet%20another%20reason%20that%20it%20pays%20to%20quit%20well.%20Here%20are%20three%20things%20to%20consider%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22618a6315-0a9e-402f-bfef-eeebceb3fbd8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20quit%20on%20a%20bad%20day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20having%20a%20lousy%20time%20at%20work%2C%20don't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-i-quit-my-job-quiet-quit-rage-quit-career-advice-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equit%20on%20a%20bad%20day%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20Laura%20Labovich%2C%20who%20runs%20an%20outplacement%20firm%20in%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20run%20away%20from%20a%20bad%20workplace%2C%20but%20they%20have%20nothing%20to%20run%20towards%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Labovich%20said%2C%20create%20a%20plan%20for%20leaving.%20Unless%20you're%20in%20a%20toxic%20work%20environment%2C%20considering%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarted-consulting-career-accenture-now-independent-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewhat%20you%20want%20to%20do%3C%2Fa%3E%20next%20is%20often%20a%20lot%20easier%20while%20you%20still%20have%20a%20paycheck%20and%C2%A0benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESketching%20out%20a%20strategy%20before%20you%20pull%20the%20ripcord%20also%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20have%20to%20stay%20forever.%20Most%20workers%20don't.%20Younger%20baby%20boomers%20held%20an%20average%20of%2012.9%20jobs%20from%20ages%2018%20to%2058%2C%20the%20Labor%20Department%20reported.%20It%20also%20found%20that%20the%20oldest%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20those%20born%20in%20the%20early%201980s%20%E2%80%94%20had%20nine%20jobs%2C%20on%20average%2C%20from%20age%2018%20to%20their%20mid-30s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f20aa1c5-54d9-4d7d-8ec5-054b8ed949a7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20go%20off%20message%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20heading%20for%20the%20door%2C%20it's%20wise%20to%20show%20gratitude%2C%20thank%20your%20boss%20and%20others%20for%20the%20opportunity%2C%20and%20explain%20why%20the%20role%20might%20no%20longer%20be%20an%20ideal%20fit%20for%20you%2C%20said%20Jim%20Detert%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Virginia's%20Darden%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business%20Administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20to%20frame%20it%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-not-afraid-ai-will-take-my-job-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efocus%20on%20advancement%20opportunities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20not%20threatening%20to%20those%20you're%20leaving%20behind%2C%20and%20it%20allows%20them%20to%20say%20that%20there%20wasn't%20a%20great%20fit%20for%20your%20growth%20or%20passions%20at%20your%20employer%2C%20Detert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20doesn't%20make%20people%20angry%20at%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetert%20said%20that%20if%20you're%20departing%20for%20a%20management%20position%2C%20for%20example%2C%20you%20can%20credit%20your%20boss%20with%20that%20by%20saying%20they've%20inspired%20you%2C%20by%20being%20a%20solid%20mentor%2C%20to%20go%20into%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20case%2C%20Detert%20said%2C%20it's%20often%20wise%20to%20give%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20say%20things%20like%2C%20'The%20whole%20reason%20I'm%20at%20this%20stage%20now%20of%20being%20so%20ready%20for%20X%2C%20is%20that%20you%20have%20given%20me%20so%20many%20opportunities%20up%20to%20this%20point%2C'%26quot%3B%20Detert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c9bfc9b-acfd-431b-ad8e-61382fbc1aa9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20throw%20bombs%20in%20an%20exit%20interview%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20exit%20interview%20could%20be%20one%20of%20the%20last%20big%20things%20you%20do%20in%20your%20job.%20So%2C%20just%20as%20you%20want%20to%20consider%20how%20you%20leave%20things%20with%20your%20boss%2C%20it's%20smart%20to%20do%20the%20same%20with%20an%20exit%20interview%2C%20Detert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20cautioned%20against%20firing%20off%20a%20litany%20of%20complaints%20about%20the%20organization.%20That's%20because%20if%20leadership%20wasn't%20listening%20to%20you%20before%20you%20said%20you%20were%20leaving%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20to%20start%20doing%20so%20when%20you%20depart%2C%20Detert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20I've%20ever%20heard%20of%20a%20case%20where%20exit%20interviews%20were%20the%20basis%20of%20any%20meaningful%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Detert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20HR%20staffers%20tend%20to%20conduct%20exit%20interviews%2C%20rather%20than%20senior%20execs.%20That%20means%20there's%20a%20lower%20likelihood%20of%20a%20big%20payoff%20from%20carrying%20out%20%26quot%3Ba%20therapeutic%20purge%2C%26quot%3B%20Detert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20in%20his%20many%20years%20of%20studying%20the%20impact%20of%20speaking%20out%2C%20there%20are%20two%20key%20considerations%3A%20Is%20it%20safe%2C%20and%20is%20it%20worthwhile%3F%20If%20you're%20leaving%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20a%20boss%20withholding%20a%20promotion%2C%20for%20example.%20Yet%2C%20Detert%20said%2C%20you%20still%20might%20meet%20colleagues%20at%20future%20employers.%20It's%20another%20version%20of%20the%20don't-burn-a-bridge%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20that%2C%20'Now%20I'm%20leaving%20and%20it's%20safer%2C'%20you%20may%20be%20mistaken%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20abou