ed%20because%20that's%20how%20long%20it%20took%20us%20to%20gather%20all%20the%20supporting%20documents%20we%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20after%20getting%20married%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68d19d1ff9db348adc0bf0d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20married%20her%20husband%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Gigi%20Gatewood%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20green%20card%20was%20approved%20in%202018%2C%20months%20after%20the%20birth%20of%20our%20first%20child%20and%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20after%20we%20first%20applied.%20This%20card%20allowed%20me%20to%20live%20in%20the%20US%20legally%20and%20work%20for%20any%20employer%20without%20needing%20sponsorship%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20felt%20freeing.%20I%20stopped%20working%20full%20time%20as%20a%20journalist%20and%20decided%20to%20freelance%20for%20companies%20like%20Netflix%20and%20Sundance.%20This%20also%20meant%20that%20I%20wasn't%20questioned%20about%20my%20work%20every%20time%20I%20entered%20the%20US%20because%20nothing%20on%20my%20passport%20or%20green%20card%20was%20tied%20to%20an%20employer.%20And%20while%20a%20green%20card%20can%20always%20be%20removed%20by%20USCIS%2C%20it%20did%20feel%20like%20a%20more%20stable%20step%20in%20my%20immigration%20journey%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freed-hastings-backs-trump-100k-h1b-fee-limit-visas-jobs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehaving%20an%20H-1B%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222320%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mom%20and%20baby%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68d19d46183847aa39d73d0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223088%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20had%20three%20children%20in%20the%20US.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigur