3Cfigcaption%3EDennis%20Tran%20says%20it's%20painful%20when%20people%20view%20neurodivergence%20and%20disability%20as%20less%20than.%3Cp%3EDennis%20Tran%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDennis%20Tran%20says%20being%20autistic%20helped%20him%20excel%20in%20quality%20assurance%20without%20a%20tech%20degree.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETran's%20autism%20diagnosis%20in%202020%20helped%20him%20understand%20his%20unique%20problem-solving%20skills.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20now%20thrives%20in%20roles%20valuing%20neurodiversity%2C%20working%20with%20Community-led%20Autism%20Research.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Dennis%20V.%20Tran%2C%20a%2032-year-old%20research%20collaborator%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20Tran's%20employment%20history%20with%20documentation.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20diagnosed%20with%20autism%20until%20late%202020%20at%2027%20years%20old.%20But%20as%20a%20professional%20with%20autism%2C%20my%20skills%20gave%20me%20an%20edge%20in%20breaking%20into%20quality%20assurance%20(QA)%20without%20a%20tech%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20undergraduate%20studies%2C%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20QA%20was%20or%20that%20it%20could%20be%20a%20viable%20career%20option.%20After%20graduating%20in%202015%20with%20a%20degree%20in%20public%20health%20policy%2C%20I%20applied%20for%20an%20internship%20at%20a%20healthcare%20startup%2C%20and%20they%20assigned%20me%20to%20my%20first%20real%20taste%20of%20QA.%20From%20there%2C%20I%20transitioned%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-double-dip-work-two-jobs-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoftware%20QA%3C%2Fa%3E%20almost%20by%20accident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20that%20autism%20isn't%20a%20limitation.%20It%20allows%20me%20to%20innovate%2C%20problem-solve%2C%20and%20build%20systems%20that%20serve%20people%20better.%20It's%20my%20superpower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2261c0efa2-14b1-42c3-986a-0e054f976a02%5C%22%3EI%20never%20planned%20on%20working%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Irvine%2C%20I%20became%20involved%20in%20research%20labs%20and%20clinical%20research.%20I%20monitored%20metrics%2C%20kept%20experiments%20on%20track%2C%20and%20streamlined%20iPad%20processes%20in%20trials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%20and%20completing%20my%20internship%2C%20a%20marketing%20colleague%20posted%20about%20me%20on%20social%20media%20to%20help%20me%20find%20work.%20A%20QA%20software%20company%2C%20Vablet%2C%20saw%20it%20and%20took%20me%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-prompt-engineer-jobs-pay-salary-requirements-no-tech-background-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eno%20tech%20background%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20taught%20myself%20everything%20from%20scratch.%20I'd%20quickly%20glance%20over%20tutorial%20videos%20and%20the%20user%20guide%2C%20but%20most%20importantly%2C%20I%20just%20spent%20time%20playing%20and%20using%20the%20app%20and%20platforms.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20grasp%20platforms%20with%20ease%20within%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20and%20days%2C%20which%20helped%20set%20me%20up%20for%20success%20in%20my%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221ca2367d-a9de-4298-b457-d740e8e590c0%5C%22%3EBefore%20my%20autism%20diagnosis%2C%20I%20struggled%20to%20understand%20why%20I%20seemed%20to%20have%20more%20difficulty%20than%20others%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20struggled%20with%20forming%20deep%20connections%20and%20friendships.%20After%20college%2C%20it%20became%20even%20lonelier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20excelling%20in%20my%20QA%20role%2C%20the%20job%20ultimately%20became%20repetitive%2C%20and%20I%20needed%20novelty%2C%20innovation%2C%20and%20challenge.%20%3Cspan%3EI%20worked%20at%20Vablet%20from%202016%20to%202022.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20had%20a%20difficult%20time%20finding%20a%20new%20job%20elsewhere.%20I'd%20send%20applications%2C%20but%20nothing%20landed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20family%20member%20suggested%20I%20might%20be%20autistic%2C%20I%20went%20to%20fill%20out%20questionnaires%20with%20a%20psychiatrist%20and%20was%20formally%20diagnosed.%20I%20started%20to%20understand%20I'd%20been%20living%20a%20neurodivergent%20life%20all%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20I%20learned%20the%20statistic%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fautismsociety.org%2Femployment%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E85%25%20of%20college%20grads%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20autism%20are%20unemployed%20or%20underemployed.%20I%20realized%20my%20brain%20works%20differently.%20I%20could%20accomplish%20tasks%20in%20months%20that%20employers%20thought%20required%20five%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20fit%20their%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20often%20call%20me%20unique%20and%20rare.%20My%20diagnosis%20gave%20me%20a%20sense%20of%20empowerment%2C%20but%20it%20negatively%20affected%20my%20self-esteem%20and%20worth%2C%20as%20I%20kept%20getting%20turned%20down%20for%20jobs.%20Because%20I%20couldn't%20get%20a%20full-time%20job%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20a%20failure%2C%20despite%20my%20previous%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cc729b2b-a746-49a0-a5b8-17b4a8c5e8f9%5C%22%3EAfter%20my%20diagnosis%2C%20I%20had%20to%20unmask%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%20diagnosis%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20thrive%20and%20coexist%20with%20my%20disability%20%26amp%3B%20neurodivergence%2C%20so%20I%20reached%20out%20to%20a%20life%20coach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20working%20with%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-coach-self-doubt-tips-finding-right-fit-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elife%20coach%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20started%20my%20own%20podcast%20and%20journey%20to%20help%20others%2C%20and%20this%20le